  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yemen: Strengthening Capacity to Investigate Human Rights Violations</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To enhance quality for monitoring, documenting, investigating and reporting by the National Commission of human rights violations and violations under international humanitarian law. 2) To enhance preparedness of the National Commission for its potential future role and mandate.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The National Commission&#x2019;s members and staff at both the headquarters and in the field, in addition to public prosecutors who are involved in investigating documented violations. 
Indirect beneficiaries: Victims of violations, including women, children and other vulnerable groups.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to improve monitoring, documentation, investigation and reporting on human rights violations and violations under international humanitarian law in Yemen.</narrative>
  </description>
